article.headline: Pennsylvania 66, Cornell 49
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber had 14 points and five steals to lead Penn to a 66-49 win over Cornell Friday night. Steve Danley and Mark Zoller each scored 10 points for the Quakers (16-8, 9-1 Ivy), who won their 14th straight game against the Big Red. After taking a 33-25 halftime lead, the Quakers opened the second half with an 18-6 run that put them up by 20 with 10:51 remaining. Cornell could get no closer than 14 the rest of the way. Penn shot 50 percent and held Cornell to 35 percent shooting. Andrew Naeve led the Big Red (11-13, 6-5) with 10 points.
